        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 4:53PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pueblo Depot, or 11 miles east of Pueblo Airport, moving east at 60
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Avondale, Pueblo Depot, Fowler, Boone, and Pueblo Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM MDT for
southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
